  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        on a bank of 207 stroke patients serum samples, and also on 40 healthy controls. The
        samples were collected during the acute phase of the ischemic event.
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  stroke diagnosis

          -  blood sampling within 36hrs from the event

          -  written agreement

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  a stroke, MI or major operation prior to the current stroke

          -  hypercoagulable state known in this patient

          -  a severe chronic disease known at the time of the stroke

          -  an infection on arrival (based on anamnesis, physical exam and lab tests)

          -  thrombolytic treatment
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
